The paper deals with fundamental limits for sparse signal processing models, which involves statistical inference and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses linear and non-linear observations, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) respectively. The paper also mentions multivariate regression and missing features, which are relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) respectively.
